will design  fabricate  and characterize various NMOS  PMOS  and CMOS structures  At the beginning of their research  cadets will be trained on the proper use of computer aided design  CAD  tools  as well as all laboratory processing and testing equipment  Cadets will then have the opportunity to begin the development of their custom made devices  following the tradition of the ECE Semiconductor Device Laboratory  Interested cadets should contact COL Addington  addingtonjs vmi edu   prior to enrolling  Course capacity is 2 cadets  Instructor   Addington Credits   TBD Col  Shawn Addington Home Courses Undergrad Research Activities Grants   Publications Microelectronics Concentration EE 493 Eight Projects are now available for the Fall 2007 semester and beyond  Visit the Undergraduate Research Project List Contact Colonel Addington if you are interested in joining the Microelectronics   Semiconductor Research Team VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Maj